Sentencas: Direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells (DC-SOFCs) with the novel perovskite La0.3Sr0.7Fe0.7 Ti0.3O3-delta (LSFT) electrodes are evaluated by using biochar derived from some one-time toothpicks made of wood as fuel in different discharging modes.
Titulo: Effects of discharge mode and fuel treating temperature on the fuel utilization of direct carbon solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The constant current (CC) mode and constant resistance (CR) mode are compared with same fuel cell configuration and fuel loading.
Titulo: Effects of discharge mode and fuel treating temperature on the fuel utilization of direct carbon solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The results show that the fuel discharged in CR mode possesses larger fuel utilization (39.7%) than that in CC mode (34.5%).
Titulo: Effects of discharge mode and fuel treating temperature on the fuel utilization of direct carbon solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The biochar fuels obtained from the wood pyrolysis in Ar atmosphere for 1 h at 400 degrees C, 500 degrees C, 600 degrees C and 700 degrees C present the efficiencies of fuel utilization are 26.3%, 34.1%, 38.6% and 39.6%, respectively.
Titulo: Effects of discharge mode and fuel treating temperature on the fuel utilization of direct carbon solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: A special discharging mode is employed in this paper for DC-SOFC to test cell performance and improve fuel utilization simultaneously as well.
Titulo: Effects of discharge mode and fuel treating temperature on the fuel utilization of direct carbon solid oxide fuel cell
